All other training scripts in this repo appear to write the compressed artifact as `final_model.int8.ptz` (even when the underlying scheme changes), which can matter for downstream tooling expecting a stable filename. Consider also writing/symlinking the ternary artifact to `final_model.int8.ptz` (or otherwise matching the established `final_model.*.ptz` convention used elsewhere).
```suggestion
            f.write(tern_blob)
        # Also expose the artifact under the conventional filename used elsewhere
        try:
            if hasattr(os, "symlink"):
                if os.path.islink("final_model.int8.ptz") or os.path.exists("final_model.int8.ptz"):
                    os.remove("final_model.int8.ptz")
                os.symlink("final_model.ternary.ptz", "final_model.int8.ptz")
            else:
                raise OSError
        except OSError:
            with open("final_model.int8.ptz", "wb") as f:
                f.write(tern_blob)
```
